snippets.title: talent createCompany Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new company entity.

snippets.title: talent getCompany Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves specified company.

snippets.title: talent updateCompany Sample
snippets.description: Updates specified company.

snippets.title: talent deleteCompany Sample
snippets.description: Deletes specified company. Prerequisite: The company has no jobs associated with it.

snippets.title: talent completeQuery Sample
snippets.description: Completes the specified prefix with keyword suggestions. Intended for use by a job search auto-complete search box.

snippets.title: talent createClientEvent Sample
snippets.description: Report events issued when end user interacts with customer's application that uses Cloud Talent Solution. You may inspect the created events in [self service tools](https://console.cloud.google.com/talent-solution/overview). [Learn more](https://cloud.google.com/talent-solution/docs/management-tools) about self service tools.

snippets.title: talent createJob Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new job. Typically, the job becomes searchable within 10 seconds, but it may take up to 5 minutes.

snippets.title: talent batchCreateJobs Sample
snippets.description: Begins executing a batch create jobs operation.

snippets.title: talent getJob Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves the specified job, whose status is OPEN or recently EXPIRED within the last 90 days.

snippets.title: talent updateJob Sample
snippets.description: Updates specified job. Typically, updated contents become visible in search results within 10 seconds, but it may take up to 5 minutes.

snippets.title: talent batchUpdateJobs Sample
snippets.description: Begins executing a batch update jobs operation.

snippets.title: talent deleteJob Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the specified job. Typically, the job becomes unsearchable within 10 seconds, but it may take up to 5 minutes.

snippets.title: talent batchDeleteJobs Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a list of [Job][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job]s by filter.

snippets.title: talent listJobs Sample
snippets.description: Lists jobs by filter.

snippets.title: talent searchJobs Sample
snippets.description: Searches for jobs using the provided [SearchJobsRequest][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.SearchJobsRequest]. This call constrains the [visibility][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job.visibility] of jobs present in the database, and only returns jobs that the caller has permission to search against.

snippets.title: talent searchJobsForAlert Sample
snippets.description: Searches for jobs using the provided [SearchJobsRequest][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.SearchJobsRequest]. This API call is intended for the use case of targeting passive job seekers (for example, job seekers who have signed up to receive email alerts about potential job opportunities), and has different algorithmic adjustments that are targeted to passive job seekers. This call constrains the [visibility][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.Job.visibility] of jobs present in the database, and only returns jobs the caller has permission to search against.

snippets.title: talent listProfiles Sample
snippets.description: Lists profiles by filter. The order is unspecified.

snippets.title: talent createProfile Sample
snippets.description: Creates and returns a new profile.

snippets.title: talent getProfile Sample
snippets.description: Gets the specified profile.

snippets.title: talent updateProfile Sample
snippets.description: Updates the specified profile and returns the updated result.

snippets.title: talent deleteProfile Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the specified profile. Prerequisite: The profile has no associated applications or assignments associated.

snippets.title: talent searchProfiles Sample
snippets.description: Searches for profiles within a tenant. For example, search by raw queries "software engineer in Mountain View" or search by structured filters (location filter, education filter, etc.). See [SearchProfilesRequest][google.cloud.talent.v4beta1.SearchProfilesRequest] for more information.
